# Liquid & Shopify Core Rules

## Liquid Syntax
- Always use valid Liquid — a single syntax error breaks the entire page render
- Use `{% render 'snippet', param: value %}` — never `{% include %}` (deprecated)
- Use `{{ section.settings.key | default: 'fallback' }}` for all dynamic output
- Use `{% comment %}...{% endcomment %}` for any non-obvious logic
- Use `| escape` when outputting user-generated content
- Use `| json` when passing Liquid values into JavaScript

## Images
- Always use `{{ image | image_url: width: 800 }} ` with `image_tag` filter
- Add `loading="lazy"` to all below-fold images
- Always specify `width` and `height` to prevent CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift)
```liquid
{{ section.settings.image | image_url: width: 1200 | image_tag:
  loading: 'lazy',
  width: 1200,
  height: 600,
  alt: section.settings.image.alt
}}
```

## Metafields
- Access via `resource.metafields.namespace.key`
- Never query metafields inside `{% for %}` loops — causes N+1 performance issues
- Always check existence: `{% if product.metafields.custom.badge != blank %}`

## Pagination
- Use `{% paginate %}` for collections — Shopify caps `limit` at 20 otherwise
- Collections need pagination for more than 50 products
```liquid
{% paginate collection.products by 24 %}
  {% for product in paginate.collection %}
    {% render 'product-card', product: product %}
  {% endfor %}
  {{ paginate | default_pagination }}
{% endpaginate %}
```

## Gotchas
- `forloop.index` starts at 1, not 0 — use `forloop.index0` for zero-based
- `assign` inside a loop does not reset — initialize variables before loops
- `limit` filter on arrays caps at 20: `collection.products | limit: 20`
- Section groups: header/footer must use `{% sections 'group-name' %}`
